<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910605-0044</DOCNO><DOCID>910605-0044.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Vista Chemical Co.:   New Entity Is Slated in Bid   To Speed Merger Proposal</HL><DATE>06/05/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A3</SO><CO>   G.RWE VC</CO><MS>BASIC MATERIALS (BSC)</MS><IN>CHEMICALS, PLASTICS (CHM)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>ACQUISITIONS andamp; MERGERS, TAKEOVERS, BOARD BATTLES (TNM)</NS><GV>FEDERAL TRADE COMMISSION (FTC)</GV><RE>EUROPE (EU)GERMANY (GE)LOUISIANA (LA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)TEXAS (TX)UNITED STATES (US)WESTERN EUROPE (WEU)</RE><LP>   RWE-DEA, whose proposed merger with Vista Chemical Co.,Houston, has been delayed for months because of federalregulatory concerns, said it would form a new entity with aLouisiana company to operate the alumina business of the twocompanies.   The move is likely to satisfy concerns of the FederalTrade Commission, which has been examining the proposed $55 ashare, or $590 million, tender offer made by RWE-DEA, aGerman company. The FTC is said to be studying possibledomination by the merged companies of the alumina market,although an agency spokesman declined to comment.</LP><TEXT>   RWE-DEA and Vista said they reached agreement withDiscovery Aluminas Inc., an affiliate of Discovery ChemicalsInc. of Port Allen, La. to operate the alumina business afterthe proposed merger is completed.   Alumina is used as a catalyst in the energy and chemicalsindustry. RWE-DEA is a unit of RWE AG, a German energy andchemicals concern.   The tender offer is set to expire at 5 p.m. EDT on Fridayalthough RWE-DEA said it may be forced to further extend theoffer if the FTC declines to grant an early termination ofthe antitrust law's waiting period, scheduled to expireMonday.</TEXT></DOC>